Key Match Events: Kosovo scored the first goal in the 9th minute via Vedat Muriqi after converting a penalty.
Vedat Muriqi scored again in the 21st minute, heading in another goal after a precise cross from Donat Rrudhani.
Albion Rrahmani scored the third goal in the 48th minute following a beautiful assist from Milot Rashica.
Lumbardh Dellova sealed the 4-0 result in the 55th minute with a precise strike after a coordinated play.
Emir Sahiti had a great opportunity to score just before the end but hit the post.
Post-Match Reflections: This victory boosts the team’s morale and demonstrates the players’ commitment to giving their best in every upcoming match.
